ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Fabian was a good TF. However, the guidance that he received from the professor was poor and the material covered very disconnected from the exams and lecture.
Would recommend to IDE students and non-IDEs alike.
Good as an introductory grade course.
A theoretical economics course with reasonable forms & amount of course evaluations and a good instructor.
It is a brief introduction to international economics. I would recommend it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course solidified many of the concepts that I had learned previously, so now I feel more confident discussing international economics and finance issues.

I really like the topic of international economics so this class was beneficial to my understanding, but I think that more explanation and variations on the models we worked on could improve my knowledge of it.
As one of the core courses, International Economics provided sound grounding in the field.
Provided good core knowledge and skills
